author: gdaniels
msg: Automatically keep two messages in resources.properties up to date
reflecting the version and build date/time of the current axis.jar.
Introduce org.apache.axis.Version, which you can run from the command
line to check what version of Axis you're running.

author: scheu
msg: Made some changes to the wsdd typeMapping element so that it is
compatible with JSR 109 typeMapping.
This will simplify the sharing of deployment information.
Also changed WSDL2Java to emit typeMapping instead of beanMapping.
Here is an example typeMapping:
<typeMapping
xmlns:ns="urn:AddressFetcher2"
qname="ns:address"
type="java:samples.addr.Address"
serializer="org.apache.axis.encoding.ser.BeanSerializerFactory"
deserializer="org.apache.axis.encoding.ser.BeanDeserializerFactory"
encodingStyle="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/encoding/"
